out too, losing the pinched and withdrawn look he had as a teen. His patchy mustache had been replaced with a thick, neatly trimmed beard that made his jawline sharper and more defined. He had lost his unibrow somehow, and his eyebrows were full and well-kept, nicely setting off his bright brown eyes. Most unsettlingly, his accent had faded, leaving only a slight trace of his old bouncy cadence hiding under a vague Canadian-Bostonian mix.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;It was all a little overwhelming. The first time they met after Varun got back, Whit almost didn't believe it was the same guy. His anxious, snarky friend was gone, and this bland, confident, frustratingly relaxed man had taken his place. Somehow, while Whit had spent the last four years watching porn and playing video games, Varun had become a normie. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;It was not a welcome change.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Varun glanced around the room. Whit followed his gaze with a frustrated blush. Okay, maybe he could’ve cleaned up some of the dirty laundry. And he could’ve stood to crack open a window. But it was his own room, god damn it.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Can I fucking help you with something?” Whit said, “Or did you just come here to bother me?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Sorry,” Varun rubbed the back of his neck sheepishly, “I was just, uh, wondering what you get up to all day in here.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Whit’s cheeks went hot and he shifted uncomfortably, feeling the sticky wetness in his boxers. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Nothing, okay?” he snapped, “I was just, fucking, I don't know! Playing video games or something! What does it matter?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Varun frowned, “Bug, you should really try to get out more…” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“What about you?” said Whit, ”Where are you going all of a sudden anyway?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Varun grinned and opened the door a little wider. For the first time, Whit could see that he was dressed in an athletic tee and sweatpants. Workout gear.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Some of the guys