      <title>If I Don&amp;#8217;t Know (It Won&amp;#8217;t Hurt)</title>
      <author> Azura </author>
      <link>https://www.scribblehub.com/series/1337192/if-i-dont-know-it-wont-hurt/</link>
      <comments>https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1337192-if-i-dont-know-it-wont-hurt/chapter/1337201/#comments</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">330dbce1222786de496926550d8b369218432d90</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 14 Dec 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Himari married Alex for her money, but now that they're divorced and Himari is onto her next mark she still can't stop seeking the thrill she found in Alex.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Alex knew that Himari was her soulmate from the moment they met. She has been patient for the years after their divorce, waiting for Himari to come to her senses. But patience has its limits.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1337192-if-i-dont-know-it-wont-hurt/chapter/1337201/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;Alex&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;div class="wi_authornotes"&gt; &lt;div&gt; &lt;div class="p-avatar-wrap"&gt;&lt;a class="avatar has-link" href="/profile/19892/azura/"&gt;&lt;img id="acc_ava_change profile" alt="" src="https://cdn.scribblehub.com/avatar/s/4/ava_19892_1578802840.jpg"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="an_username"&gt;&lt;a href="/profile/19892/azura/"&gt;Azura&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div style="clear: both;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="wi_authornotes_body"&gt;  Hello lovelies! Something new and delightful here for you. A little darker, and (at least I think) the best thing I've ever written. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Some extensive (though not necessarily complete) content warnings&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div class="sp-wrap sp-wrap-default"&gt; &lt;div class="sp-head" title="Expand"&gt; Spoiler &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="sp-body folded"&gt; &lt;p&gt;Toxic/Abusive relationships. Obsessive Behavior, Reckless driving, Not wearing appropriate clothes for the weather, Sadism, Masochism, Degradation, Infidelity, Spousal abuse (a slap), Unplanned pregnancy. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;div class="spdiv"&gt;[collapse]&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Alex was getting ready for a date when the call came. When she saw her ex-wife’s name, Alex wanted so desperately to ignore it. But she knew that if she did, the nagging doubts of whether Himari had hurt herself again, or if Himari wanted to get back together would consume Alex until the next time Himari called. So, like always, Alex answered.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You can’t keep doing this, Himari,” Alex said as a greeting, already rubbing a temple in exasperation. Himari only responded at first with a sniffling cry. Alex could only grit her teeth. She hated it when Himari used crying for attention as her approach. Her sad voice grated like the warning pulses of an oncoming migraine. Alex suspected that was part of why Himari did it.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Please, Alex. Just listen. I promise, I’m not drunk this time,” Himari said finally, in that sad voice. It was nice, at least for her ex to get to the lying right away. Himari had gotten really good at hiding the effects of alcohol over the years, but Alex knew her too well, and she could hear the subtle differences in Himari’s voice, even if no one else could.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I just, I miss you so much, Alex. Do you remember the bridge? The one you proposed to me on? I promise it’s different this time, just please. I need to see you one last time,” Himari said, breaking into muffled sobs. Himari always loved doing this, bringing up places where important moments in their relationship happened to get her way. Alex knew what Himari was doing, and Himari knew that Alex knew. Himari kept doing it because it still worked. No matter how long it had been, or what Alex had going on, when Himari called, Alex came. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Yeah. Fine. I’ll meet you there in an hour,” Alex said, talking over Himari’s annoying crocodile tears. Himari’s crying instantly stopped.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Oh, good, and wear that red dress I got you. You know the one,” Himari replied, her tone radically different from before. The sadness from earlier gone like it never existed, and now she sounded unbearably smug. Before Alex could retort, Himari hung up on her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Fuck,” Alex cursed. Already sending a message to cancel her date. At least she already had her makeup done. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;b&gt;***&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;It was raining hard as Alex drove through the dark streets. As Alex parked in the empty parking lot near the bridge, her windshield wipers were going at top speed and still not keeping up with the downpour. Her headlights were the only illumination in the empty lot, and Alex groaned, pressing her forehead into her steering wheel.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I really fucking hope she doesn’t expect me to actually walk to our spot on the bridge in this shit after telling me to wear this stupid dress,” Alex muttered to herself, cursing her inability to ever tell Himari no. Thankfully, she didn’t have to wait long. Himari had always liked to make an entrance.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;As the headlights of cars flashed by along the nearby road, a figure stepped out of the darkness into the glow of Alex’s headlights. Himari strode forth like something out of a horror movie. A sharp suit with a lace shirt under the jacket that revealed more of her tan skin than it covered, and dark leather boots. She swayed her hips as she strode towards Alex, her inky black hair plastered to her face and neck by the rain.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Alex rolled her eyes; Himari was always fucking like this. She also couldn’t stop herself from biting her lip. Her eyes trailed over Himari’s figure, painfully intrigued by the way her jacket hid how much of her breasts that lace number actually covered. There was a reason Alex had driven all the way out here in her fuck-me lingerie at the drop of a hat. Was Alex still desperately, pathetically in love with her ex-wife? Maybe. Was her ex-wife still the hottest woman Alex had ever laid eyes on? Absolutely.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Himari opened the passenger door, and Alex grimaced as the cold and wet invaded her car. Himari leaned in through the open door, her grin wicked. Dark eyes, darker hair, a maroon suit. Himari was like ink, and blood, and sex.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Fancy seeing you here,” Himari drawled, like she didn’t even notice the storm soaking her clothes and whipping her hair. Like she didn’t set this all up. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Just fucking get in already. You’re going to ruin my seats,” Alex snapped. Like Himari wasn’t far worse than any amount of wind and rain. Some things you can’t wash out. Plus, she knew that it wasn’t as fun for Himari without a struggle.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Himari’s grin dropped, her expression turning serious like a switch had been flipped. She stared Alex down for several long moments, just long enough to spite Alex before she slipped into the car. Himari slammed the door behind her, and then she was in Alex’s space.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Awww, come on, darling. You know you’re happy to see me,” Himari said, leaning in close to Alex. The smell of expensive whisky on her breath. Her ex-wife’s proximity made Alex’s heart race, and her breath quicken. As much as Alex might have wished things were different, that Himari didn’t leave her for a man, Himari’s presence still affected her like nothing else ever had. That desperate part of Alex she worked hard to keep behind the mask roiled, urging her to pull Himari so close they merge into one. Alex did her best to ignore that.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Himari, we can’t keep doing this. I have a life, and you chose not to be in it,” Alex said, trying to hold onto her anger, but found it slipping through her grasp. Himari’s fingers trailed along her thigh through the high slit in the dress Himari told her to wear. Alex gripped her steering wheel hard, the leather creaking, and her knuckles going white as she fought back a moan. Himari’s fingers were ice cold and damp from the storm, but left a trail of heat in their wake as they slid up Alex’s stocking cla