 &lt;p&gt;“Do you think-”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Thank you, but… not yet,” Falke finished for her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster sighed and gave her a thumbs-up before she rounded the corner. A moment later she heard the door click shut again, and she picked up her book.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She got the same amount of reading done through this session as well: a singular, rather short page.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane came out around twenty minutes later to find Falke staring at the blank television once again, only this time, she was alert enough to notice when she had entered the living room and turned and smiled at her once she came fully into view. Internally, Falke breathed a silent sigh of relief that Ariane had swapped her sweat-slicked nightgown for one of Elster’s larger t-shirts, the long, opaque garment thankfully reaching low enough to cover everything her increasingly too-small nightgown failed to.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“We’re uh, heading to bed now,” Ariane informed her, letting out a short yawn after she finished.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The question wasn’t asked, but statements like this one implied it: did Falke want to sleep with them tonight? She was comfortable enough to do so on occasion, usually taking up the outer side of any cuddle pile they organized and forming a basket with her long arms and legs to wrap around both Elster and Ariane.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke looked down for a moment. She wasn’t sure if being near the two wives would be such a good idea while she was still burdened by desire, but as she briefly glanced back up at Ariane’s eyes and saw the optimistic glow in her eyes, she felt like she had to say yes.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;So, she nodded and stood up, and Ariane gave a short hop of excitement before pressing her palms together; Falke almost felt her systems seize up for a brief moment as Ariane’s impromptu hop sparked a noticeable ripple up her thighs, tummy, and finally chest, still visible even through the loose shirt which mostly hung off her