vidual before this. I was… a symbol, a divine one, indeed, but still ultimately a symbol. I was given a role to play, and I played it… so many seasons of nothing but administrative monotony, never being allowed to form connections, to seek out life and change, or stray from my path in any way. I was a god, but I was just as confined and trapped as every other Replika and Gestalt at the facility… but now I am free. I am liberated to be whoever I want to be. It is the start of a life, or at the very least, a new one.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“But…” Ariane returned her head forward and sank back into Falke’s body. “Have you not just traded one aspect of desire for another? Our desires?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke found Ariane’s hand and held it firmly. “I chose to be here with you both, and you chose to have me as part of your lives. That is all that matters to me.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane took a short breath and exhaled softly. “Okay… thank you…”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Afterward, Elster snorted in her sleep, and her two partners realized jointly that it would be best to keep conversation to a minimum, lest they wake her up. Ariane brought Falke’s hand to her lips again and began to gently kiss each of the digits on her hand before moving to do the same to each of her knuckles.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I’m glad you chose to come here and be with us,” Ariane as quietly as possible whispered before she kissed the palm of Falke’s hand.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke smiled under Ariane’s kisses, but the longer she went on, the more curious her displays of affection grew. She started bringing her knuckles past her lips to suck on, followed by her finger tips. She reached for Falke’s thigh behind her and rubbed her hands up and down the smooth polyethylene shell, even giving her a light squeeze once. Then, she noticed Ariane start to wiggle her hips and legs together, sighing wistfully as she let go of her hand, and through it all, Falke felt more and more tense until she finally heard the telltale sounds of rhythmic, peaceful sleeping that signaled she was finally asleep.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke finally began to relax and nod off as well, shutting down her primary systems to enter sleep mode, but right in the middle of falling asleep she felt Ariane squirm ever so gently again and snapped back fully awake. She looked over Ariane’s cheek and saw she was still asleep, but also that she still continued to wiggle and pant.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Falke…” Ariane quietly muttered, moaning softly afterward. “Touch…” she added before sighing heavily and relaxing.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane quieted down and returned to sleep, but Falke only stared at the ceiling.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She didn’t get any more sleep that night.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;…..&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster was the first to wake up in the morning, though, with Falke never having truly fallen asleep, it might have been more accurate to say she was the second. She blinked her eyes open and almost immediately saw Falke to her left lying on her back, eyes open and unblinking toward the ceiling. She tried to lean forward but came to the realization that Ariane had shifted in her sleep, and had a significant portion of her body resting atop her, with her head planted almost face down into her chest.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Falke…?” she whispered. The Replika rolled over onto her shoulder and got a good view of the situation, smiling lightly at the picture of Ariane softly sleeping and snoring into Elster’s cleavage. “Mind giving me a hand?” Elster whispered, pointing at the sleeping beauty atop her. Falke nodded.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Her forehead crystals started to glow softly as she gently cupped the back of Ariane’s head with her hand and began to carefully roll Ariane onto her back using bioresonance.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Ellie… come back…” Ariane mumbled in her sleep as she came to a rest on her back, followed by more quiet, sleepy breathing. Elster cupped her mouth and tried not to giggle too loudly at her wife’s subconscious thoughts, but Falke bit her lip hard as she saw what Ariane was doing with her hand under the covers as she slept. She tugged the covers up past Ariane’s stomach to try and give her a modicum of privacy, but in doing so she only made Elster curious, and soon she leaned her head over to watch what her wife’s fidgeting arm was doing; she quickly snapped back and pressed her hand against her mouth.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Afterward a minute of quiet, awkward silence only punctuated by Ariane briefly snorting and groaning in her sleep, Falke deftly slipped out of bed and gave herself a light stretch; a mostly unnecessary thing to do for a Replika, but also a quirk of Gestalt neural imprinting that still felt right to do.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I will go prepare breakfast,” Falke quietly stated. Elster gave her a thumbs up.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I’ll stay here for… a bit… if that’s alright,” Elster answered, briefly looking down at the still-sleeping Ariane. Falke nodded and left the room, breathing a sigh of relief as the door clicked shut behind her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She briskly walked into the kitchen, hoping that absorbing herself in cooking would take her mind off things. Her bioresonance crystals shone brightly as she assembled her tools and ingredients: She grabbed a large metal bowl and whisk with her hands as the fridge opened and a carton of milk and a few eggs floated to her workstation, followed shortly after by tubs of sugar, flour, and salt, and finally a container of cooking oil. She carefully weighed all of her measurements on a kitchen scale before adding them one at a time to the bowl, finishing by tapping the eggs on the countertop and cracking them into the bowl. Falke wetted a cloth and wrung it out so it was just damp, wrapping it around the base of her metal bowl to keep it still as she furiously beat the mixture with a whisk.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She smiled; Ariane and Elster had an electric whisk she could have used, she had gotten it for