pio; again, she ground the beans and steamed the milk using hand tools rather than the fancy espresso machine she had acquired for them, and she didn’t hesitate to draw a little latte art of a butterfly on the top of Elster’s drink.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The only thing left was to prepare the crepes. Once her crepe pan had fully pre-heated she ladled the perfect amount on, smiling as the chilled and rested mixture smoothly spread to the edges of the pan just by tilting and rotating it. She topped three plates with their own wide, thin crepe, spooned a generous helping of strawberry compote atop each, and finished her creations with a ring of whipped cream and dusted chocolate powder for maximum flourish.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She set up each of their dishes and drinks at the dinner table and let out a satisfied sigh as she absorbed the picture before her in her head. All that was left was to wait for the other two lovebirds to emerge hungry and well-rested from their bedroom.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;But they did not emerge after she knocked on the door and announced that breakfast was ready.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;After a few minutes of increasingly tense waiting she leaned her ear up to the door.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;And immediately regretted it.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She walked back to the living room and sat on the couch, staring at her own anxious reflection in the dark screen.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;After a minute of staring and tapping her hoof on the carpet below her, she finally spoke up.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Just go in there,” she said to herself.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You haven’t been invited,” her reflection answered.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I don’t need an invitation, they want me there with them.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Then why didn’t they ask you?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“They’re polite.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“They’re different.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“They care, they understand.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You’re different.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke took a moment to look down at her cold, titanium hands before she squeezed them shut. “It doesn’t matter to them.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Her reflection laughed. “It matters to you.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke clenched her eyes shut and took in a sharp breath. She briefly wondered how AEON command would feel if one of their prized Falke units, the Nation’s wunderwaffe found itself on the verge of tears, to say nothing else of the intractable number of grave sins she was guilty of simply by being in this relationship.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You’re pathetic.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She covered her face with her hands. “Be quiet,” she weakly cried.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Want to prove us wrong? Go open their door.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;After a moment to hear her voice echo in her own head, a sense of defiance overtook Falke. She did not raise to her hooves, instead, she floated herself up from the couch and straight to Ariane and Elster’s bedroom door, gently landing on the floor just as she grasped the doorknob with her hand.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She shook; her hand shook.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;After a moment of tensing up her synthetic muscles, Falke sighed dejectedly as she let go of the doorknob.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“See? Pathetic.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She was just about to turn away and head back into the kitchen when an unexpected sound froze Falke in her tracks.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The door opened behind her, and a moment later a soft, caring, and loving voice spoke out to her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Falke…? Is everything okay?” Ariane asked.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She turned around with streaks of optical lubricant fluid running down from her eyes. “No,” she croaked, but then quickly swallowed and added more clearly. “Breakfast is ready, by the way.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane nodded and stepped out of the doorway, still in nothing but Falke’s t-shirt, only now, Falke looked at nothing but her eyes. Elster followed her wife shortly after, now with a loose, white t-shirt over her top, and Falke instinctively dropped to her knees.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;They both hugged her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Do you want to talk about it?” Ariane whispered to her after their hug ended. Falke shook her head.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I’ll be okay,” she assured them both. “This is… still a lot for me.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Hey, I get it,” Elster said, giving Falke’s shoulder a light squeeze before she got back up on her hooves. “I really do,” she repeated.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke nodded. She knew Elster was telling the truth.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Come, while your meals are still warm,” Falke spoke out, forcing a smile on their lips.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;And so, she showed them to their meals.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster wasted no time in digging into her crepe. She furiously hacked off pieces with her knife and fork to shovel into her mouth, not caring that her wild eating habits were getting bits of compote syrup and whipped cream all over her cheeks and nose. Meanwhile, Ariane took a more restrained approach. She took a moment to appreciate the sweet aromas coming from her plate before she cut off a small piece of crepe, ensuring that there was some strawberry and whipped cream on it before she forked it into her mouth.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane immediately started smiling as she chewed. “How did you get to be such an amazing chef, Falke?” she asked after swallowing her first bite.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke nodded as she looked back at Ariane’s crimson eyes, also noticing out of the corner of her vision that Elster also looked at her as she continued to wolf away at her meal. She took her first bite and swallowed it, putting down her knife and fork before she answered the question.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Falke units are not intended to be just military commanders, but also as diplomatic envoys,” she explained, watching Ariane nod along as she took a quick pause to sip her espresso. “Some extremely high-ranking party officials are also provided a Falke unit to serve as a personal adjutant. For these reasons, we were additionally programmed with a high degree of culinary, etiquette, rhetorical, and linguistic expertise.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I see,” Ariane acknowledged. “And did you make use of these skills before now?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Falke nodded. “I… cooked meals for myself and… others, on occasion.” She took another sip of her espresso and smiled. “I enjoy cooking, it is… relaxing, soothing. It is something I have full control over.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I can definitely understand that,” Ariane said. She brought her glass of milk tea forward to take a sip, with some of the pearls shooting up the wide straw.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster suddenly began to choke loudly, and both Ariane and Falke turned to face her the moment she started trying to cough. Falke wasted no time; she rose from her chair and got behind Elster, pulling her up from her seat and thrusting up her abdomen with her fist, she soon spat out a nearly intact slice of strawberry, gasping for air as Falke gently lowered her back down.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Oh my god, Ellie, are you okay?” Ariane asked, leaning over the table to get a better view of her partner.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Elster gave her a weak thumbs-up with one hand while she kept the other on her throat, gently rubbing as she tried to calm down her breathing. “I’m fine,” she eventually coughed out. “Just… gotta learn to chew,” she joked.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ariane laughed alongside her, but Falke looked away, unable to join in the teasing. She had seen where Elster was looking right before she started choking: Ariane’s drink, and in particular, the straw she used to suck up the milk tea with pearls. She also caught a glimpse of what it had made Elster’s heart want.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;What she also wanted.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The rest of breakfast finished smoothly, if rather quietly, and Elster soon returned to her room to get changed for the day.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Shouldn’t you shower?” Falke heard Ariane ask as she scrubbed the dishes clean.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Gah, no time, don’t want to be late.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Alright, I’ll come help you get ready.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“A-Actually, Ari, I think I should get changed alone.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;There was a brief pause. Falke’s hand shook just as Ariane’s whispered words reached her ear.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Come on, I’ll be quick, I promise.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The bedroom door clicked shut soon after, and Falke gasped as she stopped holding her breath. She tried to focus on cleaning all of the plates, pans, and cutlery she used in making her meal, but as she dredged her scrub brush in the hot, soapy water, she was reminded of an inescapable fact.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Her hands didn’t feel the heat of the water.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;They were mechanical hands, an artificial creation like the rest of her, nothing but metal and clockwork. Even if some parts of her body could be called organic, and she possessed most of the senses of a Gestalt, and looked like one at a glance, there was no escaping that she was not human.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;But they were.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She laid the plate in her hand back in the sink and gripped the countertop, sighing softly.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She didn’t want to consider it, but a new thought wouldn’t leave her mind.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Maybe she had made a mistake.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
